INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '36416b8b-00f4-43cf-8af8-34e60e188808',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Cypress Snapshot Testing — When It Helps vs When It Becomes Noise$escape$,
  $escape$Cypress doesn't ship snapshot testing natively — you need `cypress-image-snapshot` for pixel-level comparisons or `@cypress/snapshot` for serialized DOM diffs. Visual snapshots via `cy.matchImageSnapshot()` shine for catching unintended layout regressions in stable, design-system components: buttons, cards, nav bars. Run them inside `cy.mount()` component tests in isolation, where the DOM is fully deterministic.

The noise starts when you snapshot pages with dynamic content — timestamps, user avatars, A/B flags, or animations mid-frame. Every CI run produces a different baseline diff, turning your suite into a churn machine. The `failureThreshold` option lets you tolerate minor pixel variance, but abusing it defeats the purpose.

Practical rules: snapshot at the component level, never the full page. Use the `clip` option to scope to a stable region. Gate visual snapshot runs behind a `CYPRESS_SNAPSHOTS` env flag so they don't block every PR — run them nightly or on merges to `main` only. For DOM structure assertions, prefer `cy.get('[data-testid]').should('exist')` over serialized snapshots — DOM diffs break on any minor render change and produce unreadable output.$escape$,
  $escape$// cypress/component/Button.cy.tsx
import { mount } from 'cypress/react'

it('matches visual snapshot for primary Button', () => {
  mount(<Button variant="primary" label="Submit" />)

  // Scope to component bounds — avoids browser-chrome pixel noise
  cy.get('[data-testid="button"]').matchImageSnapshot('button-primary', {
    failureThreshold: 0.01,
    failureThresholdType: 'percent',
    clip: { x: 0, y: 0, width: 200, height: 60 },
  })
})

// In cypress.config.ts: gate behind env flag
// env: { CYPRESS_SNAPSHOTS: process.env.CYPRESS_SNAPSHOTS ?? false }$escape$,
