INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '8b15b7b4-041a-4c66-ad0f-4cfcba7b7580',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Cypress cy.intercept() — Network Mocking, Cross-Browser Runs, and Time-Travel Debugging$escape$,
  $escape$Cypress handles network interception at the browser level via cy.intercept(), giving you full control over request matching, response stubbing, and spy assertions — no proxy setup required.

Use cy.intercept() with an alias to assert on request timing and payload. Unlike Playwright's route(), Cypress waits declaratively: cy.wait('@alias') blocks until the intercepted request resolves, preventing flaky assertions on async UI.

For cross-browser coverage, pass --browser firefox or --browser edge to the Cypress CLI. Component tests and E2E specs run identically across Chromium-family browsers, Firefox, and Electron — the same cy.intercept() hooks apply everywhere without browser-specific conditionals.

Cypress's built-in Test Runner is its trace viewer equivalent. Every command is snapshotted — click the step in the Command Log to time-travel back to that DOM state, inspect the network request body, and see exactly what the app rendered. Combine this with cy.intercept({ log: true }) to surface request/response details inline in the log. No separate trace file to download; debugging is live in the browser.$escape$,
  $escape$// Intercept, alias, stub, and assert — works across Chrome, Firefox, Edge
cy.intercept('POST', '/api/search', (req) => {
  req.alias = 'searchReq';
  req.reply({
    statusCode: 200,
    body: { results: [{ id: 1, title: 'Cypress Rocks' }] },
    delay: 100,
  });
});

cy.get('[data-cy=search-input]').type('Cypress');
cy.get('[data-cy=search-btn]').click();

// Blocks until the aliased request completes — no arbitrary cy.wait(ms)
cy.wait('@searchReq').its('request.body').should('deep.equal', { q: 'Cypress' });
cy.get('[data-cy=result-title]').should('contain', 'Cypress Rocks');$escape$,
  $escape$javascript$escape$,
